The problem of finding a set of vertices to delete in order to obtain a tree is a classic problem in graph theory and has connections to many different areas of computer science. The use of algebraic reduction rules suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. The fact that the problem is NP-complete and hard to approximate suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-categories. Finally, the problem has connections to graph theory and optimization, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
